Interface NamedNodeMap

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    TNamedNodeMap

    public interface NamedNodeMap
    Objects implementing the NamedNodeMap interface are used to represent collections of nodes that can be accessed by name. Note that NamedNodeMap does not inherit from NodeList. Objects contained in an object implementing NamedNodeMap may also be accessed by an ordinal index.
    Author:
    Tomas Kunovsky
